OL,3,C'My mum has become my patient': The
OL,4,Cunpaid carers calling for recognition
OL,6,FShe said: "It's awful. You never want
OL,7,Fto do it. No one would sit there and
OL,8,Fwillingly say 'I would take on that
OL,9,Frole.'
OL,11,F"You damage that relationship. Yes,
OL,12,Fshe's my mum, but, as awful as it
OL,13,Fsounds, she becomes like your patient.
OL,15,F"The relationship that you should have
OL,16,Fbreaks down and it's emotionally
OL,17,Fheartbreaking."
OL,19,FFiona meets others like her at the
OL,20,FForum, a carer-led support group.
