OL,3,C'My mum has become my patient': The
OL,4,Cunpaid carers calling for recognition
OL,6,FThey have created a leaflet for GPs to
OL,7,Fidentify patients who should be
OL,8,Fclassed as carers, even if they do not
OL,9,Fsee themselves in that way.
OL,11,FStefan Sarbutt became a carer for
OL,12,Fwife, Penny, when she suffered a brain
OL,13,Finjury after falling down stairs.
OL,15,FHe said: "I have taken over the care
OL,16,Fof a lady that was fully functioning.
OL,17,FShe could do all sorts of things, she
OL,18,Fwas a deputy ward manager at Grimsby
OL,19,Fhospital.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/7
